<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<Algorithm code="             1. If the decimal representation of _n_ has 20 or fewer significant digits, return 𝔽(_n_).             1. Let _option1_ be the mathematical value denoted by the result of replacing each significant digit in the decimal representation of _n_ after the 20th with a 0 digit.             1. Let _option2_ be the mathematical value denoted by the result of replacing each significant digit in the decimal representation of _n_ after the 20th with a 0 digit and then incrementing it at the 20th position (with carrying as necessary).             1. Let _chosen_ be an implementation-defined choice of either _option1_ or _option2_.             1. Return 𝔽(_chosen_).           ">
